values: The voice gateway charges for the actual number of call minutes it processes. You can purchase entitlement in multiples of one thousand minutes on a monthly basis. For more details on pricing, please contact your IBM sales rep ... or call 1 ... 8 ... 7 ... 7 ... 4 ... 2 ... 6 ... 3 ... 7 ... 7 ... 4. Would you like to know more about the voice gateway?

The Voice Gateway is architected as two independently scalable micro services. To be able to deploy these two micro services you need a Docker environment such as Coo bur net ees or IBM Spectrum conductor for containers. This can either be on premises or in a cloud of your choosing. Note that although the voice gateway can be run in either location, the Watson services which it communicates with are only available in the cloud in IBM Bluemix. Would you like to know more?

The Voice Gateway supports two broad use cases. The first is a self-service agent which can interact directly with a caller using natural language. Self-service agents are built with the Watson Conversation service. The voice gateway can also act as a more passive agent assistant. In this mode, the voice gateway can listen in on a conversation between a caller and agent, producing a real-time transcription of the phone call which can be used to provide useful feedback to the agent in real-time. Would you like to know more about the self service agent, the agent assistant capability, or both?

values: There's a lot of options when it comes to security and the voice gateway. When installed on premise, the voice gateway uses SSL for all connections out to Watson cloud services. The gateway can tunnel through a forwarding proxy or it can connect using an MPLS circuit using mutual authentication. Please refer to the documentation for details on how to configure security for the voice gateway. Do you have any more questions about the voice gateway?

There are multiple alternatives to configure security for the voice gateway. When installed on premise, the voice gateway uses SSL for all connections out to Watson cloud services. The voce gateway can tunnel through a forwarding proxy or it can connect using an MPLS circuit using mutual authentication. Please refer to the voice gateway documentation available on the internet for details on how to configure security. Do you have any more questions about the voice gateway?
The voice gateway can handle multiple calls at the same time. The limit to what it can handle is based on the number of CPU cores it is running on - we average 30 simultaneous calls per CPU core ...

The Voice Gateway capacity is mainly defined by the number of simultaneous calls that the solution will need to process. Currently, the Voice Gateway can handle an average of 30 concurrent calls per each CPU core. As an example, a typical 8-core system could handle up to 240 simultaneous calls. You can expand the number of CPU kernels horizontally to support the total number of simultaneous calls required by your specific application ...
